From: Martin Schwidefsky <schwidefsky@de.ibm.com>
Subject: 3com: make 3c59x depend on HAS_IOPORT
Patch-mainline: v3.8-rc1
Git-commit: a573ea56a9b014e3ab09c44ccb659ba6d538b81e
References: bnc#802343, FATE#83037, ltc#83040

The 3com driver for 3c59x requires ioport_map. Since not all
architectures support IO port mapping make 3c59x dependent on HAS_IOPORT.

Signed-off-by: Martin Schwidefsky <schwidefsky@de.ibm.com>
Acked-by: John Jolly <jjolly@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/Kconfig |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/net/Kconfig
@@ -728,7 +728,7 @@ config ELMC_II
 
 config VORTEX
 	tristate "3c590/3c900 series (592/595/597) \"Vortex/Boomerang\" support"
-	depends on NET_VENDOR_3COM && (PCI || EISA)
+	depends on NET_VENDOR_3COM && (PCI || EISA) && HAS_IOPORT
 	select MII
 	---help---
 	  This option enables driver support for a large number of 10Mbps and
